    <string name="onboarding_title_welcome">Setup RuMDA</string>
    <string name="onboarding_description_welcome">RuMDA needs to be granted two specific permissions : notifications and wireless debugging.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_helper_welcome">We will walk through these granting to allow using RuMDA correctly.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_title_notifications">Allow notifications first</string>
    <string name="onboarding_description_notifications">RuMDA uses notifications to guide pairing and keep its background work visible. It will also be used to warn you about potential malicious behavior.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_helper_notifications">Please click on the following button and allow RuMDA to send you notifications.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_title_wireless">Turn on wireless debugging</string>
    <string name="onboarding_description_wireless">RuMDA depends on wireless debugging to executes its commands. RuMDA is not able to work correctly without that permission, that has to be given again at each start up.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_helper_wireless">Click on the following button and turn on wireless debugging. Then allow wireless debugging on this network. </string>
    <string name="onboarding_title_pairing">Pair this phone with RuMDA</string>
    <string name="onboarding_description_pairing">The pairing service listens for the pairing code from Android, so RuMDA can establish a trusted ADB relationship and reuse it later.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_helper_pairing">Start pairing, enter the code shown by wireless debugging, then return here for the reconnect step.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_title_connecting">Checking the ADB connection</string>
    <string name="onboarding_description_connecting">RuMDA is ready to auto-connect as soon as the device exposes wireless debugging and the pairing is valid.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_helper_connecting">If the reconnect does not succeed right away, try the pairing step once more.</string>
    <string name="onboarding_title_ready">Setup complete</string>
    <string name="onboarding_description_ready">RuMDA can now try connecting to ADB on launch.</string>
